28 class MeetupServiceImpl @Inject()(protected val dbConfigProvider: DatabaseConfigProvider,
29                            applicationConfig: ApplicationConfig,

34     extends MeetupService {
35 
36   val log = Logger("service.meetup")
37 
38   val format = new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss")
39 
40   val c = catService
41   
42   lazy val categoryMap = Map(
43       "movements" -> List(),
44       "education" -> List(c.science),
45       "book-clubs" -> List(c.lecture,c.reading),
46       "food" -> List(),
47       "parents-family" -> List(),
48       "fashion-beauty" -> List(),
49       "film" -> List(c.culture),
50       "photography" -> List(),
51       "health-wellness" -> List(),
52       "beliefs" -> List(),
53       "career-business" -> List(),
54       "arts-culture" -> List(c.culture),
55       "lgbtq" -> List(),
56       "music" -> List(c.culture),
57       "outdoors-adventure" -> List(),
58       "writing" -> List(c.lecture),
59       "games-sci-fi" -> List(),
60       "social" -> List(),
61       "sport-fitness" -> List(),
62       "language" -> List(),
63       "dancing" -> List(),
64       "tech" -> List(c.tech))
65       
66   def getEventData(group: String, id: String): Future[Option[Model.Event]] = {
67     val request = ws.url(config.url + group + "/events/" + id)
68       .addQueryStringParameters("key" -> config.apiKey, "fields" -> "time,photo_album,group_category")
69       
70     val result = request.get()
71 
72     result.map { case x =>
73       log.debug("Got response from meetup api: " + x.body)
74       val res = x.json.validate[Model.Event]
75       log.debug(res.toString())
76       res.asOpt
77     }
78   }
79 
80   def getEvent(url: String, login: Login): Future[Option[EventDetail]] = {
81     val t = new URI(url).getPath.split("/")
82     val i = t.indexOf("events")
83     getEventData(t(i-1),t(i+1)).map(_.map(x => toEventDetail(x)))
84   }
85 
86   def canImport(url: String, login: Login) = {
87     val uri = new URI(url)
88     val split = uri.getPath.split("/").indexOf("events")
89     (uri.getHost.equals("www.meetup.com") || uri.getHost.equals("www.meetup.de")) && split >= 0
90   }
91 
92   def toEventDetail(data: Model.Event): EventDetail = {    
93     val loc = data.venue.map(x => Location(None, x.name, Some(x.lat), Some(x.lon),
94                             x.country, x.city, x.street.getOrElse(x.address_1.getOrElse("")), None,
95                             x.phone, None, None, x.zip))
96 
97     val from = new Timestamp(data.time)
98 
99     lazy val descText = XhtmlParser(new BufferedSource(new ByteArrayInputStream(("<p>" ++ data.description ++ "</p>").getBytes))).text
100     
101     val description = data.plain_text_no_images_description
102       .orElse(data.plain_text_description)
103       .getOrElse(descText)
104     
105     val categories = categoryMap.getOrElse(data.group.category.shortname,List()) ++ List(c.meetup)
106     
107     EventDetail(None, data.name, from,
108                 None, description,
109                 Organizer(None,"Organizer",-1,None), categories,
110                 None, loc.getOrElse(Location(None,"",None,None,"","","",None,None,None,None,None)),
111                 data.photo_album.map(_.photo_sample).getOrElse(List()).map(x => TaggedImage(None,None,None,Some(x.photo_link))), 0,
112                 None, None) //TODO Prices
113   }
114 }
